         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the seed of Buddhahood the whole world</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>19</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... upon seeing (the Bodhisattva, some speak to each other), surprised and supported by each other</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (Behold:) this [is] Indra, who has left the air space provided with his riding animal Airāvaṇa</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... through [his] unique love he draws the thought of humans to him.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1967a"/><citedRange>71</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (Some) say: This here [is] the king’s son, prince Mūkaphalgu by name.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>149</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they do not understand. Thereupon some, being up on the [roofs? of the] houses, five-fold</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in all happy eras enjoying divine adorations </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>141</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (our life) we (relinquish (?)). Our wish [and] love for you, master, [is] more than (that) for the self</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1986"/><citedRange>128</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... like [his? one’s?] own life. 1. Thereupon others again (are saying in) great (love (?)) to the prince:</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... if he accumulated [his] love of all things</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>34</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1972"/><citedRange>461</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... love [and] reverence that cannot be extended to someone else. The decision</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (Thereupon (?)) the princess Snehākṣi, a girl, exceedingly shy (?)</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
